post_text:
Congratulations to our Girls and Boys Track Teams and to our students in Golf who will be participating at the State Track and State Golf Meets this year!

We will have six students from Ethan who will be participating at the State Track Meet this Friday in Spearfish and at Rapid City on Saturday. They are Patience Nesheim, Mollie Miiller, Adaya Plastow, Brady Hawkins, and Evan Weeman, with Parker Hanselman as an alternate, along with the seven students from Parkston.

Our girls‚Äô golf team members, who will be participating in Watertown at the State B Golf Tournament on June 4 and 5, will be Ally Feiner, Kailey Feiner, Regan Gerlach, and Ryanna Clauson. Our lone boys‚Äô golf member participating will be Zach Clauson.

Congratulations and Good Luck to all of them! They are representing Ethan (in golf) and Ethan/Parkston (in track) very well! May they have continued SUCCESS at State!

post_text:
Preschool Screening Announcement

The Ethan School District in cooperation with the Cornbelt Cooperative and Head Start is pleased to announce a preschool screening scheduled for April 17th for all children ages 3-5 years old.

If you have a child between the ages of birth and 2 years 11 months old and want a developmental screening completed, please contact Shannon Nelson, Birth to 3 Service Coordinator at Shannon.Nelson@usd.edu or call (605) 202-0100.

The screening is the responsibility of the local school district and will be provided at not cost to all participating children.

Contact Terry Eckstaine, Ethan Elementary Principal at (605) 227-4211 if you have questions.

post_text: If you have a child between the ages of 2.5-5 years that are not currently enrolled in Ethan School, and you have not received a screening letter, please call the school and get your child on our list. (Talk to Mary 227-4211.) We will be screening all children in the Ethan district that are eligible for preschool for the 2018-19 school year AND the 19-20 school year on April 17. Ethan currently offers a 3 year old COOP preschool (for children who are on an IEP), 4 year old preschool, and 5 year old Jr. Kindergarten.

The National Honor Society is partnering with CHS Farmers Alliance to host a food drive this year. The drive will run now through Thursday, March 15. We are accepting non-perishable food items that have not expired. Elementary students
can bring their items to their classrooms. Middle & high school students should drop them off in their adviser‚Äôs room. 7th Grade to Mrs. Gustafson, 8th Grade to Mr. Aisenbrey, Freshmen to Mrs. Frerichs, Sophomores to Mr. Roth, Juniors to Mrs. Jarding, and Seniors to Mrs. Hostler. The winners will receive a pizza party provided by CHS Farmers Alliance. The food that is collected will be donated to the Salvation Army and the Mitchell Area Safe house. Thank you for your support!

CHS is also holding an online Schwan‚Äôs fundraiser. When ordering, go to Schwanscares.com ID36447 or campaign name
Harvest for Hunger. So if you order Schwan‚Äôs please take this opportunity to support this cause. Thank you!

Paisley is the 6 month old daughter of Steven and Brooke King and the granddaughter of Scott and Stacy Zoss and Robert and Lorraine King.. Paisley was recently diagnosed with liver cancer and is undergoing treatment. We hope to see you there!!
